output_list.impact: Integer overflow in mintToken function allows the owner to set the balance of an arbitrary user to any value.
freezeAccount function allows the owner to set the freeze status of an arbitrary user, which can be used to create role-based access controls.
setPrices function allows the owner to set the price of the buy option, which can be used to create price-based access controls.
Integer overflow in buy function allows user to set the balance of an arbitrary user to any value.
selfdestructs function allows the owner to delete the contract, providing a user-controlled destructor.
getEth function allows user to extract arbitrary amount of eth from contract owner.
